    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1213817654" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1213817654" />
    <a title="George" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21007191-george"><img alt="George" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1542795267p2/21007191.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1213817654?book_show_action=true">Jul 13, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="George" class="user" itemprop="url" name="George" href="/user/show/21007191-george">George</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780374100148" href="/book/show/3115359-2666">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1213817654" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15669762940109639559"><i>2666</i> is not Christ on the cross, not the “masterpiece,” but rather one or both of the flanking thieves conceived as symmetry that conceals.<br/><br/>Bolaño has been quoted as eloquently stating that magic realism “stinks,” which evokes the carbuncled teenager rebelling against the paterfamilias. In this case, the god known as Gabo who hovers over all of Spanish literature and who runs a monopoly on the word ‘solitude.’ This rebellion, or whatever you want to call it, has resulted in a book that is manacli</span>
  <span id="freeText15669762940109639559" style="display:none"><i>2666</i> is not Christ on the cross, not the “masterpiece,” but rather one or both of the flanking thieves conceived as symmetry that conceals.<br /><br />Bolaño has been quoted as eloquently stating that magic realism “stinks,” which evokes the carbuncled teenager rebelling against the paterfamilias. In this case, the god known as Gabo who hovers over all of Spanish literature and who runs a monopoly on the word ‘solitude.’ This rebellion, or whatever you want to call it, has resulted in a book that is manacling itself. There are so many instances in this novel where the magic within realism wants to break out but is muted muzzled mummified.<br /><br />I could tell very early on that the appeal of this book would have to come from accumulation alone and not from any sentence-level pyrotechnics, of which there are little to none. While yes, the cold calculated sparse prose style has a deadening effect in a book about the dead, the beauty of the novel as an art form is that it can accommodate polyphony. The pulseless prose makes the varied locations in the book feel almost identical. Yet there were shining moments, intermittent scintillations that evoked the mystical yet hyper-real prose of Don DeLillo. Indeed, this felt like the Spanish <i>Underworld</i>, albeit diluted.<br /><br />Although mentioned in tandem at times, <i>2666</i> is no <i>Infinite Jest</i>, which is itself an LSD schizo version of <i>Underworld</i>. Rather, in trying to evoke a grave new world, <i>2666</i> becomes a grave period, with a tombstone one glances at and moves on, except for those ‘friends’ and ‘relatives’ who stay to scrutinize the lapidary lettering, to worship the manicured grass that, placed anywhere else, would be deemed ordinary. As far as I can tell, I’m a passerby on the way to Egyptian catacombs.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15669762940109639559" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

